An is a relation that is reflexive, symmetric, and transitive.
For example, ""x" divides "y"" is a partial, but not a total order on natural numbers formula_96 ""x" < "y"" is a strict total order on formula_96 and ""x" is parallel to "y"" is an equivalence relation on the set of all lines in the Euclidean plane.

