Relations may be ranked by the Schein rank which counts the number of concepts necessary to cover a relation. Structural analysis of relations with concepts provides an approach for data mining.


The idea of a difunctional relation is to partition objects by distinguishing attributes, as a generalization of the concept of an equivalence relation. One way this can be done is with an intervening set formula_110 of indicators. The partitioning relation formula_111 is a composition of relations using relations formula_112 Jacques Riguet named these relations difunctional since the composition "F G" involves univalent relations, commonly called "partial functions".

