When "R" is a partial identity relation, difunctional, or a block diagonal relation, then fringe("R") = "R". Otherwise the fringe operator selects a boundary sub-relation described in terms of its logical matrix: fringe("R") is the side diagonal if "R" is an upper right triangular linear order or strict order. Fringe("R") is the block fringe if R is irreflexive (formula_145) or upper right block triangular. Fringe("R") is a sequence of boundary rectangles when "R" is of Ferrers type.

